{"label":"Word Meanings","id":"word-meaning-5","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"meanings-1","type":"slides2","label":"Word Meanings","commonData":{"title":"Word Meanings","displayType":"custom","autoPlay":false,"substep":false},"data":[{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"accurate"},"- characterized by perfect conformity to fact or truth",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe scientist's measurements were highly <i><b>accurate</b></i>, with minimal margin for error.<br><br>\nA good dictionary provides <i><b>accurate</b></i> definitions and examples of words."}],[{"type":"title","text":"address"},"- to speak or write to someone",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\n    I will <i><b>address</b></i> the issue with the customer and find a solution.<br><br>\n    She <i><b>addressed</b></i> the audience with a heartfelt speech."}],[{"type":"title","text":"afford"},"- have the financial means to do something or buy something",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nAfter years of hard work, they could finally <i><b>afford</b></i> their dream vacation.<br><br>\nIt's important to <i><b>afford</b></i> opportunities for education to all, regardless of their background."}],[{"type":"title","text":"alert"},"- warn or arouse to a sense of danger",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe lifeguard's job is to <i><b>alert</b></i> swimmers to potential dangers in the water.<br><br>\nAn <i><b>alert</b></i> was issued to residents about an approaching storm."}],[{"type":"title","text":"analyze"},"- carefully observe, investigate, or study something to gain a deeper understanding",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nScientists <i><b>analyze</b></i> data to draw meaningful conclusions from their research.<br><br>\nThe detective needed to <i><b>analyze</b></i> the evidence to solve the mystery."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"ancestor"},"- individuals to whom a person is related by blood or descent",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nGenealogy enthusiasts often research their <i><b>ancestors</b></i> to learn about their family history.<br><br>\nOur distant <i><b>ancestors</b></i> faced many challenges in their daily lives."}],[{"type":"title","text":"annual"},"- occurring every year",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe <i><b>annual</b></i> holiday parade is a beloved tradition in our town.<br><br>\nThe company holds its <i><b>annual</b></i> shareholders' meeting to discuss business matters."}],[{"type":"title","text":"apparent"},"- clear, obvious, easily seen or understood",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe smile on her face made her happiness <i><b>apparent</b></i> to everyone in the room.<br><br>\nThe reasons for the problem became <i><b>apparent</b></i> after a thorough investigation."}],[{"type":"title","text":"appropriate"},"- suitable for a particular person, place, or situation",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nIt's important to choose <i><b>appropriate</b></i> clothing for different weather conditions.<br><br>\nUsing <i><b>appropriate</b></i> language is essential in professional communication."}],[{"type":"title","text":"arena"},"- a large stage for open-air sports or entertainments",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe <i><b>arena</b></i> was filled with excited fans cheering for their favorite sports team.<br><br>\nThe new <i><b>arena</b></i> hosts concerts, sports events, and cultural performances."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"arrest"},"- take into custody",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe police had to <i><b>arrest</b></i> the suspect after a thorough investigation.<br><br>\nThe <i><b>arrest</b></i> was made in accordance with the law and legal procedures."}],[{"type":"title","text":"ascend"},"- travel up",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nClimbers often <i><b>ascend</b></i> steep mountains with great determination and skill.<br><br>\nThe hot air balloon began to <i><b>ascend</b></i> into the clear blue sky."}],[{"type":"title","text":"assist"},"- give help; be of service",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nVolunteers <i><b>assist</b></i> in disaster relief efforts to provide support to affected communities.<br><br>\nA friendly neighbor was always willing to <i><b>assist</b></i> with household tasks."}],[{"type":"title","text":"attempt"},"- make an effort",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nDespite the challenges, she was determined to <i><b>attempt</b></i> her dream of starting a business.<br><br>\nAn <i><b>attempt</b></i> to set a new world record was met with excitement and anticipation."}],[{"type":"title","text":"attractive"},"- pleasing to the eye or mind",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe picturesque landscape of the countryside was incredibly <i><b>attractive</b></i>.<br><br>\nA well-designed website is more <i><b>attractive</b></i> to users and visitors."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"balance"},"- a state of equilibrium or equipoise; equal distribution of weight",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe gymnast demonstrated incredible <i><b>balance</b></i> on the narrow beam.<br><br>\nMaintaining a <i><b>balance</b></i> between work and personal life is essential for well-being."}],[{"type":"title","text":"barrier"},"- a structure or object that blocks free movement",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe wall served as a <i><b>barrier</b></i> to keep intruders out of the property.<br><br>\nLanguage should not be a <i><b>barrier</b></i> to understanding and connecting with others."}],[{"type":"title","text":"benefit"},"- something that promotes well-being",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nRegular exercise has many <i><b>benefits</b></i> for physical and mental health.<br><br>\nOne of the <i><b>benefits</b></i> of the new policy is improved access to healthcare."}],[{"type":"title","text":"bias"},"- a partiality that prevents objective consideration of an issue or situation",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nIt's important for journalists to avoid <i><b>bias</b></i> and report the news objectively.<br><br>\nThe judge's decision was made without any <i><b>bias</b></i> or prejudice."}],[{"type":"title","text":"bond"},"- a connection that fastens things together",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe strong <i><b>bond</b></i> between the two friends was evident in their unwavering support for each other.<br><br>\nChemical reactions often involve the breaking and forming of <i><b>bonds</b></i> between atoms."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"brief"},"- of short duration or distance",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe meeting was <i><b>brief</b></i>, lasting only 15 minutes.<br><br>\nShe provided a <i><b>brief</b></i> summary of the main points in the report."}],[{"type":"title","text":"bulk"},"- indicates that something is large or takes up a significant part of something",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe <i><b>bulk</b></i> of the project involved extensive research and data analysis.<br><br>\nBuying items in <i><b>bulk</b></i> can often save money in the long run."}],[{"type":"title","text":"capacity"},"- the ability to perform or produce",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe new factory has the <i><b>capacity</b></i> to produce thousands of units per day.<br><br>\nA person's <i><b>capacity</b></i> to learn and adapt is remarkable."}],[{"type":"title","text":"category"},"- a way to group or classify things that share certain characteristics or attributes",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThere are numerous <i><b>categories</b></i> of books in the library, including fiction, non-fiction, and reference.<br><br>\nThe food competition had a <i><b>category</b></i> for the best dessert creation."}],[{"type":"title","text":"cease"},"- put an end to a state or an activity",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe cease-fire agreement brought a temporary <i><b>cease</b></i> to the conflict.<br><br>\nShe decided to <i><b>cease</b></i> her involvement in the project due to other commitments."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"challenge"},"- a demanding or stimulating situation",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nSolving complex puzzles can be a great <i><b>challenge</b></i> for the mind.<br><br>\nOvercoming this obstacle was the <i><b>challenge</b></i> of a lifetime."}],[{"type":"title","text":"channel"},"- a pathway through which information flows",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe internet is a powerful <i><b>channel</b></i> for sharing knowledge and connecting people worldwide.<br><br>\nShe changed the <i><b>channel</b></i> on the television to find a different program."}],[{"type":"title","text":"characteristic"},"- a distinguishing quality or trait",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nHonesty is a key <i><b>characteristic</b></i> of a trustworthy person.<br><br>\nOne <i><b>characteristic</b></i> of tropical climates is high humidity."}],[{"type":"title","text":"cite"},"- to quote as an authority or example",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nIn your research paper, remember to <i><b>cite</b></i> your sources to give credit to the original authors.<br><br>\nThe author <i><b>cited</b></i> several historical documents to support the argument."}],[{"type":"title","text":"civil"},"- relating to ordinary citizens and their concerns",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\n    <i><b>Civil</b></i> rights movements have played a crucial role in achieving equality for all people.<br><br>\nThe dispute was resolved through <i><b>civil</b></i> negotiations rather than legal action."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"clarify"},"- to make clear and understandable",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nCan you <i><b>clarify</b></i> your instructions? I'm not sure what you mean.<br><br>\nThe manager needed to <i><b>clarify</b></i> the company's new policy for the employees."}],[{"type":"title","text":"classic"},"- something that has stood the test of time and remains relevant, valuable, or appreciated across generations",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\n\"To Kill a Mockingbird\" is considered a <i><b>classic</b></i> novel of American literature.<br><br>\n<i><b>Classic</b></i> cars from the 1950s are highly sought after by collectors."}],[{"type":"title","text":"coincide"},"- to occur at the same time or place",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nOur vacation plans <i><b>coincide</b></i> with the local festival, so we'll get to experience it.<br><br>\nThe meeting will <i><b>coincide</b></i> with her business trip, making it convenient for her."}],[{"type":"title","text":"collapse"},"- to fall down or give way suddenly",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe old building was in such disrepair that it was in danger of <i><b>collapse</b></i>.<br><br>\nThe stock market saw a sudden <i><b>collapse</b></i> due to economic factors."}],[{"type":"title","text":"colleague"},"- an associate or coworker, especially in a professional setting",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nMy <i><b>colleague</b></i> and I have been collaborating on this project for several months.<br><br>\nShe introduced me to her <i><b>colleagues</b></i> at the conference."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"calculate"},"- make a mathematical computation",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nStudents need to <i><b>calculate</b></i> the total sum of the numbers in this equation.<br><br>\nTo determine the cost, you must <i><b>calculate</b></i> the expenses and revenues."}],[{"type":"title","text":"capable"},"- having ability",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nShe is <i><b>capable</b></i> of handling challenging tasks with ease.<br><br>\nThe team members are all highly <i><b>capable</b></i> professionals in their respective fields."}],[{"type":"title","text":"captivity"},"- the state of being imprisoned",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe animals were kept in <i><b>captivity</b></i> for research purposes.<br><br>\nThe explorer described his experiences in <i><b>captivity</b></i> during his expedition."}],[{"type":"title","text":"carefree"},"- without trouble or worry",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe children played <i><b>carefree</b></i> in the park, enjoying the sunny day.<br><br>\nDuring the vacation, we embraced a <i><b>carefree</b></i> attitude and left our worries behind."}],[{"type":"title","text":"century"},"- a period of 100 years",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe historical artifact dates back to the 18th <i><b>century</b></i>.<br><br>\nWe've entered a new <i><b>century</b></i> filled with technological advancements."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"chamber"},"- a natural or artificial enclosed space",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe hidden treasure was found in a secret <i><b>chamber</b></i> deep within the castle.<br><br>\nThe sound echoed through the empty <i><b>chamber</b></i>."}],[{"type":"title","text":"circular"},"- having a circular shape",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe Earth follows a <i><b>circular</b></i> orbit around the Sun.<br><br>\nThe wheels of the bicycle were <i><b>circular</b></i> in design."}],[{"type":"title","text":"coax"},"- influence or persuade by gentle and persistent urging",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nShe tried to <i><b>coax</b></i> her cat out of hiding with a treat.<br><br>\nThe manager had to <i><b>coax</b></i> the team into accepting the new project."}],[{"type":"title","text":"column"},"- a line of units following one after another",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe newspaper has a regular <i><b>column</b></i> for opinion pieces.<br><br>\nThe soldiers marched in a straight <i><b>column</b></i>."}],[{"type":"title","text":"communicate"},"- convey or share information, thoughts, ideas, or feelings with someone else or a group of people",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nPeople use various forms of language to <i><b>communicate</b></i> with each other.<br><br>\nThe new technology makes it easier to <i><b>communicate</b></i> across long distances."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"competition"},"- the act of contending with others for rewards or resources",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe Olympic Games are a showcase of international <i><b>competition</b></i>.<br><br>\nBusinesses often engage in <i><b>competition</b></i> to gain market share."}],[{"type":"title","text":"complete"},"- having all necessary qualities",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe puzzle is not <i><b>complete</b></i> without all the missing pieces.<br><br>\nTo succeed, you need a <i><b>complete</b></i> understanding of the subject."}],[{"type":"title","text":"concentrate"},"- make denser, stronger, or purer; giving full and undivided attention to something",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe chef had to <i><b>concentrate</b></i> the sauce to enhance its flavor.<br><br>\nIt's important to <i><b>concentrate</b></i> on your studies to excel in your exams."}],[{"type":"title","text":"concern"},"- something that interests you because it is important",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nEnvironmental <i><b>concerns</b></i> have led to a push for sustainability.<br><br>\nThe safety of the employees is a top <i><b>concern</b></i> for the company."}],[{"type":"title","text":"conclude"},"- bring to a close",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe meeting will <i><b>conclude</b></i> with a summary of the decisions made.<br><br>\nAt the end of the trial, the judge will <i><b>conclude</b></i> the proceedings."}]]}]},{"label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"matchByDragDrop","id":"drag-drop-1","lockAfter":1,"commonData":{"title":"Drag the correct option in each blank to form meaningfull sentences.","fontSize":"1rem"},"data":["The scientist's measurements were highly *accurate*, with minimal margin for error.\nI will *address* the issue with the customer and find a solution.\nAfter years of hard work, they could finally *afford* their dream vacation.\nThe lifeguard's job is to *alert* swimmers to potential dangers in the water.\nScientists *analyze* data to draw meaningful conclusions from their research.","Genealogy enthusiasts often research their *ancestors* to learn about their family history.\nThe *annual* holiday parade is a beloved tradition in our town.\nThe smile on her face made her happiness *apparent* to everyone in the room.\nIt's important to choose *appropriate* clothing for different weather conditions.\nThe *arena* was filled with excited fans cheering for their favorite sports team.","The police had to *arrest* the suspect after a thorough investigation.\nClimbers often *ascend* steep mountains with great determination and skill.\nVolunteers *assist* in disaster relief efforts to provide support to affected communities.\nDespite the challenges, she was determined to *attempt* her dream of starting a business.\nThe picturesque landscape of the countryside was incredibly *attractive*.","The gymnast demonstrated incredible *balance* on the narrow beam.\nThe wall served as a *barrier* to keep intruders out of the property.\nRegular exercise has many *benefits* for physical and mental health.\nIt's important for journalists to avoid *bias* and report the news objectively.\nThe strong *bond* between the two friends was evident in their unwavering support for each other.","The meeting was *brief*, lasting only 15 minutes.\nThe *bulk* of the project involved extensive research and data analysis.\nThe new factory has the *capacity* to produce thousands of units per day.\nThere are numerous *categories* of books in the library, including fiction, non-fiction, and reference.\nThe *cease*-fire agreement brought a temporary cease to the conflict.","Solving complex puzzles can be a great *challenge* for the mind.\nThe internet is a powerful *channel* for sharing knowledge and connecting people worldwide.\nHonesty is a key *characteristic* of a trustworthy person.\nIn your research paper, remember to *cite* your sources to give credit to the original authors.\n*Civil* rights movements have played a crucial role in achieving equality for all people.","Can you *clarify* your instructions? I'm not sure what you mean.\n\"To Kill a Mockingbird\" is considered a *classic* novel of American literature.\nOur vacation plans *coincide* with the local festival, so we'll get to experience it.\nThe old building was in such disrepair that it was in danger of *collapse*.\nMy *colleague* and I have been collaborating on this project for several months.","Students need to *calculate* the total sum of the numbers in this equation.\nShe is *capable* of handling challenging tasks with ease.\nThe animals were kept in *captivity* for research purposes.\nThe children played *carefree* in the park, enjoying the sunny day.\nThe historical artifact dates back to the 18th *century*.","The hidden treasure was found in a secret *chamber* deep within the castle.\nThe Earth follows a *circular* orbit around the Sun.\nShe tried to *coax* her cat out of hiding with a treat.\nThe newspaper has a regular *column* for opinion pieces.\nPeople use various forms of language to *communicate* with each other.","The Olympic Games are a showcase of international *competition*.\nThe puzzle is not *complete* without all the missing pieces.\nThe chef had to *concentrate* the sauce to enhance its flavor.\nEnvironmental *concerns* have led to a push for sustainability.\nThe meeting will *conclude* with a summary of the decisions made."]},{"type":"completeWord","id":"complete-word-1","label":"Complete Word","data":["Characterized by perfect conformity to fact or truth | ACCURATE\nTo speak or write to someone | ADDRESS\nHave the financial means to do something or buy something | AFFORD\nWarn or arouse to a sense of danger | ALERT\nCarefully observe, investigate, or study something to gain a deeper understanding | ANALYZE\nIndividuals to whom a person is related by blood or descent | ANCESTOR\nOccurring every year | ANNUAL\nClear, obvious, easily seen or understood | APPARENT\nSuitable for a particular person, place, or situation | APPROPRIATE\nA large stage for open air sports or entertainments | ARENA","Take into custody | ARREST\nTravel up | ASCEND\nGive help; be of service | ASSIST\nMake an effort | ATTEMPT\nPleasing to the eye or mind | ATTRACTIVE\nA state of equilibrium or equipoise; equal distribution of weight | BALANCE\nA structure or object that blocks free movement | BARRIER\nSomething that promotes well-being | BENEFIT\nA partiality that prevents objective consideration of an issue or situation | BIAS\nA connection that fastens things together | BOND","Of short duration or distance | BRIEF\nIndicates that something is large or takes up a significant part of something | BULK\nThe ability to perform or produce | CAPACITY\nA way to group or classify things that share certain characteristics or attributes | CATEGORY\nPut an end to a state or an activity | CEASE\nA demanding or stimulating situation | CHALLENGE\nA pathway through which information flows | CHANNEL\nA distinguishing quality or trait | CHARACTERISTIC\nTo quote as an authority or example | CITE\nRelating to ordinary citizens and their concerns | CIVIL","To make clear and understandable | CLARIFY\nSomething that has stood the test of time and remains relevant, valuable, or appreciated across generations | CLASSIC\nTo occur at the same time or place | COINCIDE\nTo fall down or give way suddenly | COLLAPSE\nAn associate or coworker, especially in a professional setting | COLLEAGUE\nMake a mathematical computation | CALCULATE\nHaving ability | CAPABLE\nThe state of being imprisoned | CAPTIVITY\nWithout trouble or worry | CAREFREE\nA period of 100 years | CENTURY","A natural or artificial enclosed space | CHAMBER\nHaving a circular shape | CIRCULAR\nInfluence or persuade by gentle and persistent urging | COAX\nA line of units following one after another | COLUMN\nConvey or share information, thoughts, ideas, or feelings with someone else or a group of people| COMMUNICATE\nThe act of contending with others for rewards or resources | COMPETITION\nHaving all necessary qualities | COMPLETE\nMake denser, stronger, or purer; giving full and undivided attention to something | CONCENTRATE\nSomething that interests you because it is important | CONCERN\nBring to a close | CONCLUDE"]},{"id":"meanings-2","type":"slides2","label":"Word Meanings","commonData":{"title":"Word Meanings","displayType":"custom","autoPlay":false,"substep":false},"data":[{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"confuse"},"- mistake one thing for another",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe similar-sounding words can easily <i><b>confuse</b></i> new language learners.<br><br>\nDon't <i><b>confuse</b></i> the two different routes; one leads to the beach, and the other to the forest."}],[{"type":"title","text":"congratulate"},"- say something to someone that expresses praise",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nWe should <i><b>congratulate</b></i> the team on their remarkable victory.<br><br>\nHe sent a card to <i><b>congratulate</b></i> his friend on their new job."}],[{"type":"title","text":"considerable"},"- large in number, amount, extent, or degree",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe project required a <i><b>considerable</b></i> amount of time and resources.<br><br>\nThe storm caused <i><b>considerable</b></i> damage to the coastal town."}],[{"type":"title","text":"content"},"- satisfied or showing satisfaction with things as they are",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nAfter a fulfilling meal, he felt <i><b>content</b></i> and happy.<br><br>\nBeing <i><b>content</b></i> with what you have can lead to a more peaceful life."}],[{"type":"title","text":"contribute"},"- give, provide, or supply something",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nMany people volunteered to <i><b>contribute</b></i> food and clothing to the charity.<br><br>\nEach team member can <i><b>contribute</b></i> their unique skills to the project."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"crafty"},"- someone who is clever, cunning, or devious, often with an intent to deceive or manipulate others",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe <i><b>crafty</b></i> fox outwitted the hunters and escaped with the prize.<br><br>\nShe used her <i><b>crafty</b></i> negotiation skills to secure a better deal."}],[{"type":"title","text":"create"},"- bring into existence",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nArtists often <i><b>create</b></i> beautiful works of art that inspire and move people.<br><br>\nScientists work tirelessly to <i><b>create</b></i> innovative solutions to global challenges."}],[{"type":"title","text":"demonstrate"},"- give an exhibition of to an interested audience",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe inventor will <i><b>demonstrate</b></i> the new technology at the product launch.<br><br>\nTeachers often <i><b>demonstrate</b></i> problem-solving techniques to their students."}],[{"type":"title","text":"descend"},"- move downward and lower, but not necessarily all the way",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe hikers began to <i><b>descend</b></i> the steep mountain trail as the sun set.<br><br>\nThe plane will <i><b>descend</b></i> to a lower altitude as it prepares for landing."}],[{"type":"title","text":"desire"},"- the feeling that accompanies an unsatisfied state",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nHis <i><b>desire</b></i> for adventure led him to explore remote places and cultures.<br><br>\nThe <i><b>desire</b></i> for knowledge drives many to pursue education and learning."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"destructive"},"- causing damage",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nNatural disasters like hurricanes can be highly <i><b>destructive</b></i> to communities.<br><br>\nThe use of <i><b>destructive</b></i> weapons in warfare has devastating consequences."}],[{"type":"title","text":"develop"},"- progress or evolve through a process of natural growth",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nChildren <i><b>develop</b></i> physically and intellectually as they grow into adulthood.<br><br>\nScientific research helps us <i><b>develop</b></i> new technologies and understanding."}],[{"type":"title","text":"disaster"},"- an event resulting in great loss and misfortune",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nEarthquakes and tsunamis are natural <i><b>disasters</b></i> that can have widespread devastation.<br><br>\nThe company faced a financial <i><b>disaster</b></i> due to poor management decisions."}],[{"type":"title","text":"disclose"},"- expose to view as by removing a cover",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe government decided to <i><b>disclose</b></i> classified information for public safety.<br><br>\nIt's essential to <i><b>disclose</b></i> potential conflicts of interest in business dealings."}],[{"type":"title","text":"distract"},"- draw someone's attention away from something",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe noisy construction outside the window would <i><b>distract</b></i> her from her work.<br><br>\nIt's best not to <i><b>distract</b></i> the driver when they are behind the wheel."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"distress"},"- a state of adversity",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nProviding relief to those in <i><b>distress</b></i> is a humanitarian mission.<br><br>\nThe loss of a loved one can cause profound emotional <i><b>distress</b></i>."}],[{"type":"title","text":"entertain"},"- provide amusement for",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nComedians use humor to <i><b>entertain</b></i> their audiences and make them laugh.<br><br>\nThe circus aims to <i><b>entertain</b></i> both children and adults with acrobatics and performances."}],[{"type":"title","text":"create"},"- bring into existence",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nArtists often <i><b>create</b></i> beautiful works of art that inspire and move people.<br><br>\nScientists work tirelessly to <i><b>create</b></i> innovative solutions to global challenges."}],[{"type":"title","text":"demonstrate"},"- give an exhibition of to an interested audience",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe inventor will <i><b>demonstrate</b></i> the new technology at the product launch.<br><br>\nTeachers often <i><b>demonstrate</b></i> problem-solving techniques to their students."}],[{"type":"title","text":"descend"},"- move downward and lower, but not necessarily all the way",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe hikers began to <i><b>descend</b></i> the steep mountain trail as the sun set.<br><br>\nThe plane will <i><b>descend</b></i> to a lower altitude as it prepares for landing."}],[{"type":"title","text":"desire"},"- the feeling that accompanies an unsatisfied state",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nHis <i><b>desire</b></i> for adventure led him to explore remote places and cultures.<br><br>\nThe <i><b>desire</b></i> for knowledge drives many to pursue education and learning."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"destructive"},"- causing damage",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nNatural disasters like hurricanes can be highly <i><b>destructive</b></i> to communities.<br><br>\nThe use of <i><b>destructive</b></i> weapons in warfare has devastating consequences."}],[{"type":"title","text":"develop"},"- progress or evolve through a process of natural growth",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nChildren <i><b>develop</b></i> physically and intellectually as they grow into adulthood.<br><br>\nScientific research helps us <i><b>develop</b></i> new technologies and understanding."}],[{"type":"title","text":"disaster"},"- an event resulting in great loss and misfortune",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nEarthquakes and tsunamis are natural <i><b>disasters</b></i> that can have widespread devastation.<br><br>\nThe company faced a financial <i><b>disaster</b></i> due to poor management decisions."}],[{"type":"title","text":"disclose"},"- expose to view as by removing a cover",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe government decided to <i><b>disclose</b></i> classified information for public safety.<br><br>\nIt's essential to <i><b>disclose</b></i> potential conflicts of interest in business dealings."}],[{"type":"title","text":"distract"},"- draw someone's attention away from something",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe noisy construction outside the window would <i><b>distract</b></i> her from her work.<br><br>\nIt's best not to <i><b>distract</b></i> the driver when they are behind the wheel."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"distress"},"- a state of adversity",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nProviding relief to those in <i><b>distress</b></i> is a humanitarian mission.<br><br>\nThe loss of a loved one can cause profound emotional <i><b>distress</b></i>."}],[{"type":"title","text":"dusk"},"- the time of day immediately following sunset",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe park becomes tranquil and serene at <i><b>dusk</b></i>, as the day transitions into night.<br><br>\nMany nocturnal animals become active at <i><b>dusk</b></i>."}],[{"type":"title","text":"eager"},"- having or showing keen interest or intense desire",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe students were <i><b>eager</b></i> to learn and participate in the class discussion.<br><br>\nThe young explorer was <i><b>eager</b></i> to embark on his first adventure."}],[{"type":"title","text":"ease"},"- freedom from difficulty or hardship or effort",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nRelaxing by the beach provides a sense of <i><b>ease</b></i> and tranquility.<br><br>\nA well-organized workspace can enhance productivity and make tasks more <i><b>ease</b></i>."}],[{"type":"title","text":"entertain"},"- provide amusement for",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nComedians use humor to <i><b>entertain</b></i> their audiences and make them laugh.<br><br>\nThe circus aims to <i><b>entertain</b></i> both children and adults with acrobatics and performances."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"enlighten"},"- give someone greater knowledge and understanding about a subject or situation",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe purpose of education is to <i><b>enlighten</b></i> individuals and expand their horizons.<br><br>\nThe mentor sought to <i><b>enlighten</b></i> the young artist about the subtleties of their craft."}],[{"type":"title","text":"enthusiasm"},"- intense and eager enjoyment, interest, or approval",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe crowd's <i><b>enthusiasm</b></i> for the concert was evident through their cheers and applause.<br><br>\nShe tackled her work with great <i><b>enthusiasm</b></i> and dedication."}],[{"type":"title","text":"establish"},"- set up (an organization, system, or set of rules) on a firm or permanent basis",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nThe company aims to <i><b>establish</b></i> itself as a leader in the tech industry.<br><br>\nGovernments work to <i><b>establish</b></i> laws and regulations for the welfare of their citizens."}],[{"type":"title","text":"evaluate"},"- assess or judge the value, importance, quality, or condition of something",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br>\nTeachers <i><b>evaluate</b></i> their students' progress through various assignments and tests.<br><br>\nBefore making a decision, it's important to carefully <i><b>evaluate</b></i> all available options."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"flexible"},"- able to bend easily",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nYoga practitioners often have <i><b>flexible</b></i> bodies, allowing them to perform various poses with ease.<br><br> \nThe gymnast's <i><b>flexible</b></i> movements impressed the judges."}],[{"type":"title","text":"focus"},"- the concentration of attention or energy on something",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nTo succeed in your studies, you need to maintain a high level of <i><b>focus</b></i> and avoid distractions.<br><br> \nThe photographer's <i><b>focus</b></i> was on capturing the perfect shot."}],[{"type":"title","text":"fragile"},"- easily broken or damaged or destroyed",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nHandle the glassware with care; it's <i><b>fragile</b></i> and can shatter easily.<br><br> \nThe antique vase was beautiful but <i><b>fragile</b></i> and required delicate handling."}],[{"type":"title","text":"frantic"},"- marked by uncontrolled excitement or emotion",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nWhen they realized they were running late for the flight, they became <i><b>frantic</b></i> and rushed to the airport.<br><br> \nThe news of the championship win sparked <i><b>frantic</b></i> celebrations in the city."}],[{"type":"title","text":"frequent"},"- coming at short intervals or habitually",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nThe bus service provides <i><b>frequent</b></i> trips to and from the city center, making commuting convenient.<br><br> \nThey had <i><b>frequent</b></i> meetings to discuss project progress."}]]},{"steps":[[{"type":"title","text":"frontier"},"- a wilderness at the edge of a settled area of a country",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nExplorers once embarked on dangerous journeys to discover the <i><b>frontier</b></i> and expand their knowledge of the world.<br><br> \nThe town was located near the <i><b>frontier</b></i>, where the untamed wilderness began."}],[{"type":"title","text":"furious"},"- marked by extreme anger",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nHis rude remarks left her <i><b>furious</b></i>, and she demanded an apology.<br><br> \nThe unfair treatment of the employees led to a <i><b>furious</b></i> protest."}],[{"type":"title","text":"generosity"},"- the trait of being willing to give your money or time",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nHis <i><b>generosity</b></i> was evident when he donated a substantial amount to the charity.<br><br> \nShe is known for her <i><b>generosity</b></i> in helping those in need."}],[{"type":"title","text":"hail"},"- precipitation of ice pellets",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nIn severe weather, <i><b>hail</b></i> can cause damage to crops and vehicles.<br><br> \nThe unexpected <i><b>hail</b></i> storm surprised the residents of the area."}],[{"type":"title","text":"hardship"},"- something difficult to endure",{"type":"html","text":"Eg: <br><br> \nThe family faced financial <i><b>hardship</b></i> during the economic downturn and had to make sacrifices.<br><br> \nOvercoming personal <i><b>hardship</b></i> often leads to personal growth."}]]}]},{"label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"matchByDragDrop","id":"drag-drop-2","lockAfter":1,"commonData":{"title":"Drag the correct option in each blank to form meaningfull sentences.","fontSize":"1rem"},"data":["The similar-sounding words can easily *confuse* new language learners.\nWe should *congratulate* the team on their remarkable victory.\nThe project required a *considerable* amount of time and resources.\nAfter a fulfilling meal, he felt *content* and happy.\nMany people volunteered to *contribute* food and clothing to the charity.","The *crafty* fox outwitted the hunters and escaped with the prize.\nArtists often *create* beautiful works of art that inspire and move people.\nThe inventor will *demonstrate* the new technology at the product launch.\nThe hikers began to *descend* the steep mountain trail as the sun set.\nHis *desire* for adventure led him to explore remote places and cultures.","Natural disasters like hurricanes can be highly *destructive* to communities.\nChildren *develop* physically and intellectually as they grow into adulthood.\nEarthquakes and tsunamis are natural *disasters* that can have widespread devastation.\nThe government decided to *disclose* classified information for public safety.\nThe noisy construction outside the window would *distract* her from her work.","Providing relief to those in *distress* is a humanitarian mission.\nThe park becomes tranquil and serene at *dusk*, as the day transitions into night.\nThe students were *eager* to learn and participate in the class discussion.\nRelaxing by the beach provides a sense of *ease* and tranquility.\nComedians use humor to *entertain* their audiences and make them laugh.","The purpose of education is to *enlighten* individuals and expand their horizons.\nThe crowd's *enthusiasm* for the concert was evident through their cheers and applause.\nThe company aims to *establish* itself as a leader in the tech industry.\nTeachers *evaluate* their students' progress through various assignments and tests.\nYoga practitioners often have *flexible* bodies, allowing them to perform various poses with ease.","To succeed in your studies, you need to maintain a high level of *focus* and avoid distractions.\nHandle the glassware with care; it's *fragile* and can shatter easily.\nWhen they realized they were running late for the flight, they became *frantic* and rushed to the airport.\nThe bus service provides *frequent* trips to and from the city center, making commuting convenient.\nExplorers once embarked on dangerous journeys to discover the *frontier* and expand their knowledge of the world.","His rude remarks left her *furious*, and she demanded an apology.\nHis *generosity* was evident when he donated a substantial amount to the charity.\nIn severe weather, *hail* can cause damage to crops and vehicles.\nThe family faced financial *hardship* during the economic downturn and had to make sacrifices."]},{"type":"completeWord","id":"complete-word-2","label":"Complete Word","data":["Mistake one thing for another | CONFUSE\nSay something to someone that expresses praise | CONGRATULATE\nLarge in number, amount, extent, or degree | CONSIDERABLE\nSatisfied or showing satisfaction with things as they are | CONTENT\nGive, provide, or supply something | CONTRIBUTE\nSomeone who is clever, cunning, or devious, often with an intent to deceive or manipulate others | CRAFTY\nBring into existence | CREATE\nGive an exhibition of to an interested audience | DEMONSTRATE\nMove downward and lower, but not necessarily all the way | DESCEND\nThe feeling that accompanies an unsatisfied state | DESIRE\nCausing damage | DESTRUCTIVE","Progress or evolve through a process of natural growth | DEVELOP\nAn event resulting in great loss and misfortune | DISASTER\nExpose to view as by removing a cover | DISCLOSE\nDraw someone's attention away from something | DISTRACT\nA state of adversity | DISTRESS\nThe time of day immediately following sunset | DUSK\nHaving or showing keen interest or intense desire | EAGER\nFreedom from difficulty or hardship or effort | EASE\nProvide amusement for | ENTERTAIN\nGive someone greater knowledge and understanding about a subject or situation | ENLIGHTEN\nIntense and eager enjoyment, interest, or approval | ENTHUSIASM","Set up (an organization, system, or set of rules) on a firm or permanent basis | ESTABLISH\nAssess or judge the value, importance, quality, or condition of something | EVALUATE\nAble to bend easily | FLEXIBLE\nThe concentration of attention or energy on something | FOCUS\nEasily broken or damaged or destroyed | FRAGILE\nMarked by uncontrolled excitement or emotion | FRANTIC\nComing at short intervals or habitually | FREQUENT\nA wilderness at the edge of a settled area of a country | FRONTIER\nMarked by extreme anger | FURIOUS\nThe trait of being willing to give your money or time | GENEROSITY\nPrecipitation of ice pellets | HAIL\nSomething difficult to endure | HARDSHIP"]}]}